President Donald J. Trump has appointed a legal team to serve under White House Counsel Donald F. McGahn in matters of compliance and ethics. The team consists of Stefan C. Passantino as Deputy Assistant to the President and Deputy Counsel to the President, Uttam Dhillon, Scott Gast, and James D. Schultz as Special Assistants to the President and Associate Counsel to the President. Passantino has previously served as Chair of the Dentons Political Law team, representing corporations, interest groups, and political figures in ethics, election law, and lobbying laws. Dhillon has served as Chief Oversight Counsel for the U.S. House of Representatives Financial Services Committee and Chief of the Department of Homeland Security’s Office of Counternarcotics Enforcement. Gast has worked as Investigative Counsel to the Office of Congressional Ethics, and Schultz was Chair of Cozen O’Connor’s Government Law and Regulatory Affairs Practice Group and General Counsel of the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania. The appointment of this team reflects the importance of ethics compliance to the President and his administration.